.TH simple_shell 1 "November 2025" "Holberton School" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
simple_shell \- simple UNIX command line interpreter
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ./hsh
.br
.B simple_shell
.SH DESCRIPTION
A minimal UNIX command interpreter written in C. It runs in interactive and
non-interactive modes and executes programs via execve(2).
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
$ ./hsh
($) /bin/ls
($) exit
.fi
.PP
.nf
$ echo "/bin/ls" | ./hsh
.fi
.SH AUTHORS
See the AUTHORS file.
.SH SEE ALSO
sh(1), execve(2), fork(2), waitpid(2)
